bug.short_desc: Strange results when searching for dotted identifier

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 3937 File in which the strange matches are found
When I search the Apache Derby code for the string "derby.module.rawStore", I get a match in a file called modules.properties (attached). However, the links to the lines that match look odd. Some of them are black, others are blue, and some of them show empty lines.

Created attachment 3938 Screenshot
For those on SWAN, see here for an example: http://khepri25.norway.sun.com/source/search?q=derby.module.rawStore&project=derby
Also attaching a screenshot for those who cannot access the internal server.

There are actually two issues here:
1) The <b> and <a> tags are incorrectly nested when a match spans multiple lines
2) The FSM in PhraseMatcher can end up matching too long phrases
I'll address (1) as part of this bug, and file a new one for (2).
Filed bug #15912 for the remaining issue.
